value 2: throughout pregnancy and for three months postpartum

value 4: Flecainide 100 mg po bid was prescribed. At 34 1/7 weeks' gestational age, fetal heart rate was normal at 117 beats/min and the ascites and hydramnios had almost completely resolved. As a result, the daily dosage of flecainide was decreased to 150 mg. This was followed within a few days by the partial reformation of ascites and a recurrence of fetal supraventricular tachycardia. The dose of flecainide was increased to 200 mg/d, which led in 3 days to renewed regression of ascites and hydramnios. At 35 weeks' gestational age, the daily dosage was again reduced to 150 mg and, with no recurrence of pathology, to 100 mg (two 50-mg doses) by the 36th week until delivery at 39 5/7 weeks
